title.narrative: Program to strengthen and decentralize the national response against STIs/HiV for universal access within 5 years in the Republic of Guinea

description.narrative: Guinea - HIV - Secrétariat Exécutif du Comité National de Lutte contre le Sida de la République de Guinée - SE/CNLS. This program has the following goals: Reduce new infections by 50% from 2013 to 2017. Reduce mortality and morbility for PLwHIV by at least 50% from 2013 to 2017. The objectives of this program are: From 2013 to 2017, at least 90% of children and adults living with HIV survive 12 months after initiation of ARV treatment. From 2013 to 2017, at least 60% of key populations (MSM and PS) adopt a lower risk facing behavior STI / HIV. From 2013 to 2017, at least 60% of young teens adopt a lower risk facing behavior STI / HIV. From 2013 to 2017, the proportion of HIV transmission is reduced by 90% among children born to HIV positive mothers
